Detailed Description

A class which encodes and decodes among browfile identifier strings, browfile identifier parts, and other raw data defining browfile identifiers.

Overview

A browfile is uniquely identified by either by its identifier, or, equivalently by six parts which compose the identifier.  This class provides methods for converting back and forth among the identifier, the parts and other raw data from which the parts can be derived.

All methods provided by this class are factory methods.

Specification of a browfile's identifier in terms of its parts

An important substring of the identifier is always the exformatDotProfileName. If there is no profileName, exformatDotProfileName is simply the exformat. If there is a profileName, exformatDotProfileName is "exformat.profileName". Note that the profile name itself may have dots (.) in it.

After that, the form of the browfile identifier depends on the part extoreMedia.  This table gives that form as a function of extoreMedia:

  • BkmmExtoreBuiltIn.   This is the basic "default" case. The identifier form is simply the exformatDotProfileName.
  • BkmmExtoreOtherHome.   There are two possible sub-forms:
    • ":volume:account:exformatDotProfileName"
    • ":account:exformatDotProfileName"
    The first form is used if the volume root was mounted when the browfile was identified, and the second form is used if the home folder on another Mac was mounted. In the latter case, the volume name is unknown.
  • BkmmExtoreStandalone.   The identifier form is "file://standalonePath:exformatDotProfileName".   The standalonePath is a full path that itself begins with a slash, and contains slashes in it, up to and including the bookmarks file or folder of bookmarks files.

+ (NSString *) homePathWithParts: (NSDictionary*)  parts  

Encodes the two otherMacXXXXX values from a given a dictionary into a full filesystem path to a Home directory in the /Volumes directory.

Parameters:
parts A dictionary containing keys constKeyIdentifierOtherMacAccount and optionally constKeyIdentifierOtherMacVolume.
Returns:
The full path in one of two forms,
  • "/Volumes/VolumeName/Users/aUserShortName"
  • "/Volumes/aUserShortName"
The first form will be returned if constKeyIdentifierOtherMacVolume is present in parts and the second form will be returned otherwise.

+ (NSString *) identifierWithParts: (NSDictionary*)  parts

Parameters:
parts A dictionary containing key(s) from the constants listed in Identifier Parts Keys.
Returns:
The constructed identifier string.

+ (NSDictionary *) otherMacIdentifierPartsWithVolumesPath: (NSString*)  path  

Given the path of a file or folder, extracts the values of the constKeyIdentifierOtherMacAccount and constKeyIdentifierOtherMacVolume keys and returns them in a dictionary.

Parameters:
path A path to some file or folder in a Home directory on another Macintosh account, in one of these two forms:
  • "/Volumes/VolumeName/Users/aUserShortName/Additional/Components/Ignored"
  • "/Volumes/aUserShortName/Additional/Components/Ignored"
If a value cannot be extracted from the path, no key is set for it in the result.
Returns:
A dictionary containing neither, one, or both of the keys constKeyIdentifierOtherMacAccount, constKeyIdentifierOtherMacVolume.

otherMacVolume: (NSString*)  otherMacVolume 

Given the otherMacXXXX parts of a standalone browfile, returns the relevant substring of the identifier, either ":volume:account:" or ":account:".

+ (NSDictionary *) partsWithExformatDotProfileName: (NSString*)  string  

Given an exformatDotProfileName string, extracts the exformat and profileName to a dictionary.

The exformatDotProfileName is defined in the class description. If a value cannot be extracted from the path, no key is set for it in the result.

Parameters:
string The string from which the values will be extracted.
Returns:
A dictionary containing none, one or both of the keys constKeyIdentifierExformat, constKeyIdentifierProfileName.
